Earlier you were saying fiction.live doesn't work on mobile at all. But do you think fiction.live would be the best platform for you to write on? I flipped through a few stories and fiction.live has the author ask questions, and users submit predefined answers (basically vote on what the author says) with a separate chatbox. This is mainly used to write and have people vote on lore and the character's actions. From the stories I've read, I'd say that only fits part of what you're looking for.

Maybe a chatroom would be better for your stories, you could link in the url and start typing, folks would follow the link and make freely thought up (instead of voting for a few author-posted) suggestions towards the character's actions.
We would also appreciate reading (but not necessarily making suggestions to) your story on the thread here.
That way anyone who wants to read the story has access to it without going to another site, and the people who make suggestions will have a place where they can do that freely.

>>15228257
Let's not style this as a conflict and perseverance, but let's try to think up solutions.
